<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[86, 666, 485, 821]]<|/det|>
Evaluation in different rooms. Different room types affect the propagation of acoustic signals differently. We pick two typical room types with different reverberation effects to evaluate their impact on our attack. The results show that our samples can get similar success rates within 50 centimeters in both rooms. When the distance increases to \(1\mathrm{m}\) and beyond, the performance of our commands becomes less effective in the meeting room than in the bedroom. We suspect this is due to the stronger reverberation in the meeting room since our samples were not explicitly processed for reverberation effect.  

